        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Border Security and Migrant Safety Act of 2022</b></p> <p>This bill establishes within U.S. Customs and Border Protection a dedicated intelligence cell focused on sharing information related to (1) concentrated surges of migrants arriving at a U.S. land border, and (2) illicit smuggling and trafficking that may pose a threat to a U.S. land border. The bill also makes permanent the authority of the Department of Homeland Security to establish departmental joint task forces for various purposes.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
